{
  "texts": [
    "SSGAN [45] invented by suggest a calligraphic imagery segmentation and classification using autonomous stroking for the evaluation task.",
    "Image-to-image conversion is addressed using the strokes segmentation based generative adversarial network (SSGAN) technique.",
    "The proposed strategy efficiently produces correct results, unlike existing methods that perform poorly or are unsuitable for practical tasks.Our-GAN [46] by Yoon et al. present.",
    "The first non-repetitive 4K or higher pictures may be generated from a training image using OUR-GAN, the first one-shot ultra-high-resolution (UHR) image synthesis framework.",
    "By starting with a low-resolution picture that is visually consistent, OUR-GAN then gradually increases the resolution using super-resolution."
  ]
}